Portugal Studies Ending Madeira Subsidy, Higher Tax, Diario Says

-- B y   J o a o   L i m a
-- 
2011-09-20T06:43:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/portugal-studies-ending-madeira-subsidy-higher-tax-diario-says.html
Portugal ’s  Finance Ministry  is
studying austerity measures for the island region of Madeira
that include cutting state workers, ending a subsidy to state
workers and raising the value added tax, Diario Economico
reported, citing unidentified people in government.  The cut in the number of state workers and the tax increase
would exceed what has been determined in Portugal’s financial
aid program, the Portuguese newspaper said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
